node.title: COVID lockout restrictions extended in Greater Darwin amid concern about new exposure site
node.alt: Michael Gunner stands at a lectern during a COVID press conference.
node.description: COVID lockout restrictions in Greater Darwin will be extended by an extra 24 hours after the identification of several new exposure sites, including one authorities have labelled of "particular concern", but the lockout in Katherine is on track to end at 5pm today.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has again recorded no new cases of coronavirus, according to Chief Minister Michael Gunner.\u200b", "But he has announced that the lockout for Greater Darwin, which was due to lift at midnight tonight, will be extended for 24 hours.", "The lockout for Katherine will be lifted from 5pm today.", "But Mr Gunner said authorities are especially concerned about \"unknown close contacts\" at the Noonamah Hotel on the edge of Darwin, which was listed as a new exposure site today.", "More to come."]
